\subsubsection{Per-Class Transfer is Heterogeneous Across Lineages}

Top-level transfer is far from uniform across the three amniote lineages (Table~\ref{tab:mini_benchmark_perclass}). Under Stage~3 v4.3-singlefold --- the most realistic estimate --- DNA $F_1$ ranges from $0.40$ on zebra finch to $0.83$ on platypus, LTR $F_1$ from $0.37$ on zebra finch to $0.57$ on platypus, and LINE $F_1$ is the most stable at $0.51$--$0.71$. Stage~2 inflates each per-class number by $0.04$--$0.36$ but preserves the same lineage ordering: zebra finch is hardest in every cell. The two robust patterns across stages are (i)~LTR is the weakest top-level class on every species ($F_1$ 0.21--0.50 across the table), and (ii)~platypus generalises best, alligator second, zebra finch worst.

